adr_address: 375 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 375 11th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: DNA Lounge

reviews.text: What a gnarly place! You will have anything from burlesque shows to electronic music in a given night. Excellent bar with a super wicked house drink. There are plenty of beers on tap too. The area multiple levels and different rooms to chill in. You really can't beat this place if you are looking for a spark. Also, they have pizza 🍕 you can get next door twenty four hours a day! Check this place out next you are in San Francisco! Plenty of street parking in the area too! Let's rock and roll 🍥
This is an amazing place to not only see people you know but also see new awesome bands. I'm always so amazed at the caliber of bands there. Adjacent to awesome pizza!! Including vegan pizza!

Asked for glass of water; they said they don't give out cups and that I'd have to buy a drink.  Nickel-and-diming everything. 25% premium for tickets at the door, plus a $2 credit card fee, then $9 beers once you're inside. Booths available for purchase, which are then obviously always empty. I've always admired the owner jwz@ as an open source nerd, for his cool ideas. But no wonder this place is going out of business. Really losing touch with the funky, low-key, cheap San Francisco throwback that this place is supposed to be, not the rebellious cyberpunk haven that I expected. Now it's just a punk-ass business. I wish Jamie luck.
The events that are good are amazing. Don't bother with BOOTYSF show unless you are a straight edge blue collar yuppie though,they need their night too, and that's the one they swarm.
Had a good time a bit pircey I mean $40 for Halloween weekend and all drinks including the well $10+ that's a bit much. But overall I had a cool time.

adr_address: 270 7th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 270 7th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Sightglass Coffee

reviews.text: I'm in love with their vanilla cold brew. The coffee here is good and the pastries are delicious!! Really cool and urban atmosphere
Coffee is good. Space is better. People watching is the best. And if you're lucky, you'll get to pet someone's adorable dog outside.

I never want to leave this place, the atmosphere is so lovely. The coffee and scone are amazing. The nice young man that took my order was pleasant and he called me friend. This was my most favorite part of this SF trip. I'm not only leaving my heart in San Francisco, I'd like to leave right here. Here you go Sightglass, it's all yours ❤.
great in house roasted beans . strong and lingering after taste. second floor sitting is a bit warm tho even in winter. maybe laptops are emitting so much heat here

I just had the worst experience here. I always like their coffee, but this morning I am on the go so I ordered a cold coffee, specifying "no ice". I waited for 5 min and the guy in the counter made ice coffee full with ice. When I requested for a redo the guy arrogantly said that this is the way how they make coffee and refused to redo. I cannot stand his attitude and requested for a refund. He claimed to be the store manager, and this is beyond what I'd imagine as a coffee store manager would do. People should be respected, and his attitude disgusted me. Oh, one more thing, when I requested a refund, the guy did not refund my original payment, which is credit card, but with cash. Very Sneaky.

adr_address: 28 6th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 28 6th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Dottie's True Blue Cafe

reviews.text:
Had two breakfasts here while we were in San Francisco and could have had two more if there would not have been huge queue outside the restaurant one hour after opening. The prices were on the higher side, but for good reason. The portions were huge and really tasty and service was amazing. Although sometimes the waiters came to ask a bit too often if we would want more coffee or if anythings was okay, but of course it is better that way than to have to ask for service.

Also this place the most wonderful gluten free pancakes.

Believe the hype and the queues.

Came on a Sunday for brunch and it was packed. Staff was very kind. Food we got was well worth it. Omelettes met high expectations and fresh bread and jam were really great. Only reason one star deduction was there's no lunch service on weekends, and one with our party did not want eggs, so menu is extremely limited on weekends for someone who didn't want eggs unfortunately. Otherwise positive and we'll be back.

Hefty portion and tastes good. The toast goes well with butter and jelly together. Potatoes are tasty but nothing special. Passionate service. Boar sausage is a bit too salty. A bit pricey for breakfast. Read the special menu before reading the normal menu!

After tackling the breakfast biscuit sandwich special at Dottie's, I wasn't hungry again until dinner. There's a reason this place had a line out the door when we arrived 15 minutes after opening. Not only was the food delicious and plentiful, but the coffee was good too (they'll send you off with a to go cup at no extra charge on your way out). Our server was awesome and even though the place was packed, we never felt rushed or forgotten about. Yes, it's a little pricey, but my plate was worth every penny.

Best meal I had in San Francisco.  Had to wait outside for about 45 mins, but it was well worth it.  I had the Salmon Scrambler and was very happy I did.  The service was great as well.  Prices were very reasonable for the food and service I received.  Next time I am in town, I won't have breakfast anywhere else.

adr_address: 500 Hayes St, San Francisco, CA 94102-4214, USA
formatted_address: 500 Hayes St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: La Boulangerie de San Francisco, Hayes

reviews.text: Mostly good with some things that need a little working on. The food is always really delicious and the staff are always nice. That being said two things need help. 1) When you warm up croissants etc, they arent actually warm inside. So the cheese, chocolate, or whatever is inside, is still cold. 2) Drink orders should be taken at the start of the counter, not at the end when you are already at the register. By then, any food you got warmed up will then have to wait another 5-7min while your drink is being made. With the middle of the pastries not being all that warm to begin with, I often end up with my to-go item already cold before I can get out the door. IF I could get  a hot drink and somewhat hot food ...at the same time, it would amazing.

Good place for coffee and breakfast.  Pricey, but then again what isn't pricey in SF.  Friendly staff.  Good amount of people just taking in a good read, catching up on work, or simply enjoying the views while they have a cup of coffee or one of their many pastry options.
This chain is one of the best French bakery in SF in my opinion. The buttery croissants are wonderful. I love the fact you can get some free cornichons too.
Incredible food, friendly service and bomb coffee ...we were visiting from oregon..do you mail your beans ?? Thank you !!!
One word: YUM!  Great pastry, the real deal.

adr_address: 66 Mint St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 66 Mint St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Blue Bottle Coffee

reviews.text:
Very busy place but we managed to get a table. My wife had the avocado with chilli and lemon juice on toast and I had the poached eggs.

We both had cafe latte. The service was quick and extremely efficient. It’s difficult to get a seat as it’s busy but we can see why.

The food itself was lovely and it was great to watch the guys in the kitchen, despite us having just the above the detail that goes into the presentation is excellent.

It was roughly $33 for both of us and is about on par with other breakfast establishments in San Francisco. Worth a try!

I really like coffees made by Blue Bottle. The place is a little small though and the lines and wait time can get a bit long at times, but I would generally recommend this place. It is one of the better coffee shops in SF in my opinion.

The coffee is delicious and the inside space is hip and modern with y'all ceilings. However, there is limited seating. The location is in an okay area...just stick to hanging out in Mint Plaza but not going past 4th Street. Friendly staff who will offer suggestions. Better to take your coffee and take a walk around the city.

Expensive for what it is but hey this is San Francisco. $15 for a latte and 2 poached eggs on milk bread toast. Coffee was good and so were the eggs on toast. I'd skip the food as its more a snack not lunch food.  Just go for coffee at this place. Single origin coffee choices are great if your are a coffee fanatic and wanna try, its heaven. Even the preparation is done in a curious way.

Won't pretend to be a coffee connoisseur but have to say the coffee here is quite exceptional. I know for most coffee savants adding milk is tantamount to sacrilege but it's how I drink coffee.  They really take coffee seriously here and most employees have an almost encyclopedic knowledge of the beverage.
All in all great cups of coffee here

adr_address: 845 Market St #201, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 845 Market St #201, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Auntie Anne's Pretzels

reviews.text: Normally have a great experience at Auntie Anne's locations, but this one was a major disappointment. Not only were they out of the advertised pepperoni pretzel nuggets but they were out of the cheese dipping sauce. The only excuse to running out of one of your major dipping sauces is poor management. It's not like they have to make the cheese sauce. It doesn't even take that much room to store hundreds of the little containers.

I LOVE the Almond pretzel and my son likes the mini dogs. The staff here is really friendly and I usually have to wait like 10 minutes but it is worth it to get a fresh out of the oven pretzel. We usually get the buy 3 get one free, stamp card ready! The drinks are pretty good too so I'm a happy camper.
Love it and staff is very cool. Got a pretzel for free by just telling how much I love their Pretzldogs. Wish I could have them in Germany, too.
We bought the original and the cinnamon bites. Apart from way too much sugar on the bites, they were both very good.
How they make the pretzels taste so good, I will never know. I suspect the secret has to do with butter and sugar.

adr_address: 730 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103-3119, USA
formatted_address: 730 Howard St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Samovar Tea Lounge, Yerba Buena Gardens

reviews.text:
Incredible tea selection in SF. Food was good and clean. Unfortunately there is massive construction going on which took away from the garden ambience we heard was once there. Nice interior space, good outdoor seating, however all felt a bit corporate. 

Entrance was hard to find (look for staircase off Howard) they're located on the second floor. 

Wouldn't consider a tea "lounge" more of an extensive tea list and service that lacks the quaint charm one would have in mind for a tea lounge. 

Maybe check out their location on Valencia in the mission to enjoy the dried leaves and grab a bite in the hood.
Cute little elevated T-bar situated over looking the Moscone complex. Really great if you’re into tea, those somewhat limited options if you’re looking to explore a full bar.

I used to love this place, but the quality has been slipping in recent years. This last visit I got the quiche and a cup of lentil soup, both were painfully bland. The sandwiches used to be more filling and made with better bread, too. Not sure what's happened, but I'm willing to give them another try to return to old favorites like the Chinese and Japanese bowls and the squash dumplings.

Great place for tea at anytime of the day, with amazing views. Expensive, but you’re paying for the views too. Remains open throughout construction and garden does not look out over construction. No WiFi, but on he patio, you can connect to WiFi.

This place would be 5 stars if the service wasn't so crappy. They have open tables and I wanted to order tea for myself. They refused to serve me until my friend came even though I told them she may not even show up. 
Another time I came here my waitress forgot about me. I waited for 40 min for my check. I was fed up so I went inside and left 20 bucks with the cashier (not knowing the exact amount I even owed). They had the nerve to quickly run after me to tell me I owed them 5 more bucks.

adr_address: 599 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102-1228, USA
formatted_address: 599 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Honey Honey Cafe & Crepery

reviews.text: Big menu, and pretty affordable. Order at the counter and they will serve you your food. I didn’t get an option for a side with my sandwich. I got a California sandwich and an almond cookie for around $12. Decent service and decent atmosphere. If I lived closer it would be a place to go when I couldn’t decide.

Good options for food and drinks. The metod is ordering from the cashier, she also makes the drinks. You take your drinks to the table on your own (there are glass and water tanks near the cashier if you want water). The waiters are only there to bring you the food and cleaning the table - and they are not very eager to do anything else. It can be a 15 min wait before ordering.

This place is ok, but super overrated. The line is long and moves somewhat slowly. The crepes and other dishes I've tried are average. There are a ton of options, so it's a good place to go if you have picky eaters. They do have really good fresh orange juice. Seating for large groups is limited. Cards, cash, and NFC payments are accepted.

Long wait on a Sunday which is typical, but pretty delicious food that was worth the wait! If you order the Blintz crepe, it's definitely insta-worthy, but the inside was a bit too runny for my taste. The crab cake eggs Benedict though was delicious, and the potatoes were cooked perfectly! They also have freshly squeezed orange juice which is a plus. Giving it four stars though because I ended up finding a hair in my crab cake and they took a long time to make me a new one (or just forgot until I had to go back up there).. other than that though I would definitely come here again!

Long wait. The crab cakes were delicious.  Only reason I️ didn’t pick 5 stars is they lost our order and we waited 40 minutes for our food. Besides that I️ would say it was very good. If you try the honey honey cake, make sure they warm it up for you. It was great with coffee.

adr_address: 315 Linden St, San Francisco, CA 94102-5109, USA
formatted_address: 315 Linden St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Blue Bottle Coffee

reviews.text: This place has some of the best coffee I have ever tasted. Coffee is sourced from a variety of locations all over the world. Hand ground, pressed, and made into one the finest cups of coffee that you'll ever have. They have only a few locations so far, 3 in San Fran, 1 in Tokyo and they just opened one in NYC. Definitely gives Starbucks reserve a run for their money.
An experience. I met up with an old friend here and I just loved the simplicity of this place. We grabbed coffee and then walked around. There is a bench across the street. Totally recommend!
I tried their cold brew and it was amazing! Like absolutely amazing but if you trying for the first time then please get the cafe latte or cafe mocha! Its what they are known for.
Lovely blue bottle coffee. Can't love it more!
One point taken off as there is no filter coffee (only pour over) which is a hassle if you're in a rush. Other than that, super tasty and good pretzel croissant

adr_address: 1231 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1231 Market St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Staff was great! I got my usual of an iced coffee and it tasted a bit lighter than usual. This location has nowhere for you to sit... it only serves as a grab and go. Just FYI.

Good small starbucks.
No seating options.
Very few tables.
Good for takeaway.
Ordered chai latte... Cannot taste any chai flavor. Never had this happen at any of the other locations.
Starbucks fails at everything, as usual. Bad staff and everything tastes bad.
Nice and friendly people and the evening people always know my name. Quick and efficient service. There are 3 Starbucks near me but I always come here. I just wish the store was remodeled.

adr_address: 748 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
formatted_address: 748 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
name: Philz Coffee

reviews.text: Van Ness is a very small place unlike the Philz   in Castro and Mission. They share a space with a sandwich shop and if you want to sit, you sit in the sandwich shop. BTW, the sandwiches are delicious but they are $10 each.  The coffee is excellent.  It's just missing the ambiance of other Philz.

It's always been a feeling of amazed reward. A cup of Philz is like being brought home. It's to me the quintessential essence of a golden cup of scrumptious coffee. I can't live with out one at this point in my life!
The Batistas are always extremely chill and giving, and as for the coffee, it has easily risen to the top of my to do list. 
Thank you all and love Philz .
Steve 😊
Good third wave coffee. Loved the down to earth atmosphere at this place. Good value for your money especially if you pick up beans.

Pretty normal Philz location. There is a lounge next door, to sit and work and talk and such. Coffee was good, but it's good at all Philz locations I've been to. The Kouign Amann was really heavy, though I don't think it's made in house.
Cashier seemed bored, which is pretty abnormal for Philz, but guess he's probably having an off day
The best chamomile tea, with cream & 50% honey, I've ever had! Love it.

adr_address: 685 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94107-1601, USA
formatted_address: 685 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: The Creamery

reviews.text: Stopped by this location for quick bite before heading back to Los Angeles. Service was fast, food was of good quality, and the atmosphere gave me a cosy feeling. The chef served up a great breakfast sandwich, one if the best I've had in a while. No complaints!
Great cold brew coffee & macchiato. We had the pesto margarita creep and it was so good. Definitely recommend this place to start your day.

Friendly staff, promptly prepared and tasty breakfast.  The establishment has been in the same spot for eight years...I would take occasional coffee breaks there while at a  long ago job nearby. Such longevity for cafe speaks volumes.
awesome bartender! do try hot buttered rum if you have a sour throat. And please try their fully hands free washroom! amazing experience

4 things made the service here really terrible:

- I had to repeat the order 3 times - the staff weren't paying attention
- They forgot to add avocado to the salad (which was included on the menu)
- I asked for dressing for my salad. The waiter said he'd get it and although it wasn't busy he immediately forgot it seems - I had to go back in and remind him.
- We ordered two cappucinos. They just sat on the counter until the waiter came out and asked us if they were ours. All other items were delivered to the table so we were confused when the waiter blamed us because "The coffees are usually picked up from the counter"

Not going to come here again

The food was acceptable...

adr_address: 1122 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103-3928, USA
formatted_address: 1122 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: BrainWash

reviews.text: I'm just sad, sad, sad! Brainwash is permanently closed!! This was the best laundromat in San Francisco. Friendly staff, great food, awesome entertainment, and a clean, clean laundry facility. I wish the best of luck to all the people who made Brainwash a fun place to do your laundry!!
So sad they closed. Really good food that wasn't The New SF price. RIP little SF wonder.
Do laundry and eat brunch. Free voucher available at Hospitality House 🏠 on Sixth Street. Great staff. Excellent facilities.

Clean, well organized and pleasant, unlike most laundromats in the city. First time I went, my wife and I set all our machines up to wash, played some pinball and ordered a burger ("The Burger of Doom"). Just as we finished eating the surprisingly tasty burger, an open mic comedy night was featured on the little stage of the cafe! Pretty rad little place!
Excellent laundromat... It has a caffe and even live entertainment. It close a little early... but is well looked after.

adr_address: 399 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 399 Golden Gate Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Philz Coffee

reviews.text: Many varieties of coffees, I had a very strong one, among the strongest ever had. Well brewed. Nice cakes too, big tables to work, near little Saigon.

Freindly warm feeling coffee shop where people gather to work or just hang out. Great baristas and most importantly, coffee that will change your life!
Philz also has a great selection of quick bites and really delicious baked goods. Any Philz location would definitely hit that itchy spot.
Philz Coffee is amazing. I love the flavors imparted by the one cup / pour over method. My only issue is with the lines sometimes in the mornings, but the best comes to those who wait. ☕️
Good coffee but really, no coffee is worth $3.50. And for a small cup? Not again unless I really, really have to pee.

Terribly confusing service! Boutique drip-only coffee joint, which is all and well albeit ill-advertized. We paid and one of the orders in our party was lost all together. Waited nearly 20 for a cold pastry and a pour over. Seems to be a local staple, but would not recommend.

adr_address: 120 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 120 4th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: (I am never going to this store again) This is the second time, I walk in here. I was the second customer in line. Apparently the queue section was far back which I didn't notice. Three people walked into the store and went to the queue section. Store clerk noticed the situation. I thought, I will let three people order and order after them. More people walked into the store and store clerk did notice the situation. However, she did not say, can I help you? or You could have been next. Instead this black girl told me to go the back of the line. I denied. I told her you have seen me here for last ten minutes and that is the best response you can give. She was straight up disrespectful and ignorant. The other guy took the order. Later when I was waiting for my coffee, this black girl and her co-workers were looking at me and laughing at me. Never felt this embarrassed in a store before. (wow ! the customer service)
Impolite barista. One of them. Mixed up sequence of orders. Unpleasant communication.
It's Starbucks, you can't go wrong
Terrible staff. Very unprofessional and rude
It sucked there’s no outlet to charge your phone

adr_address: 1390 Market Street, 107, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 1390 Market Street, 107, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: The coffee is what you'd expect from Starbucks. The place isn't a good place to stay - it's tiny, and all the power outlets are simply not working. They used to have wireless charging and they are removed too.
The same as every other over priced coffee shop in SF. It's ok
I think it’s small but nice
Post finding my phone; charging it downloading the app in the new phone, and getting discount,  in Lui, notary. I couldn't use the bathroom first.smhh.ok.
Great staff and prompt service. One of the best Starbucks I have been to. Only 4 stars as their wireless charging table is not functioning and only 1 outlets for customers to use.

adr_address: 272 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 272 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Soluna Cafe & Lounge

reviews.text: Food here is alright. Nothing special and it is quite expensive actually. I paid 15$ for a small serving size of Mac n cheese which tasted like plain Mac n cheese just with fancy cheese that didn’t even taste that good. The menu choice here also does not have a lot of variety. There was about 4 choices for actual meals to eat. Also a worker here (I’m pretty sure he was the manager ) was very rude to these old ladies that had walked in when it was closing time.
Food was fair but over priced. Atmosphere practically non-existent. I was greatly underwhelmed.
Nice atmosphere. The wait staff seemed a bit thin/overworked but friendly. The steak was great. The nicoise salad was just okay as the seared tuna didn't seem fresh.
Katie & I loved the Civic Burger for a quick lunch ...and being close to Civic Center

Nice atmosphere inside and an interesting cocktail menu. But the service was super slow. We were there for over an hour before we got our entrees, which were decent but forgettable. I might stop in again for a drink at the bar, which was a good size, but likely won't return for dinner.

adr_address: 289 8th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 289 8th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Wicked Grounds

reviews.text: Awesome kinky cafe. Nice Leather and rope for sale. The staff was very sweet and friendly. The Turkey melt was bomb and the salad was delicious!! I would come here all the time if I lived in San Francisco. Definitely a place to check out.

The table was not clean, I started cleaning it myself with some paper napkins, a server walked right next to me and didn't offer help.
They serve coffee in disposable cups even when you say you are going to drink it there. Cream on the coffee was frozen cold.
The attendant who took our order didn't have the best attitude. There were literally just four people at the store and the servers didn't bother to bring items to the table, they would just call the orders out loud for us to pick them up, when we're were only 10ft away from them. Bagels took forever.
They used the same knife to cut my goat cheese bagel and my wife's cream cheese bagel, therefore, my wife's bagel tasted like goat cheese (which she hates). We were so displeased with the whole experience that we didn't even bother to tell them about the goat cheese. We just took off. 
It is expensive, not that clean, service is terrible.. I can't understand how everybody is giving 5 stars.
Hand-crafted food and beverages. Quite tasty. Welcoming environment. Great book selection.

Interesting places it's basically a fetish shop with coffee and food sounds kinda gross when you put it that way but it's super clean and the staff is really nice. The bathrooms could use a good scrub down not gonna lie. Good coffee and I heard their food is really good I didn't personally get to try it. Definitely worth the visit if you're not squeamish about sexuality.
Best cafe in the world !!! Where else are you free to be yourself and proudly let your freak flag fly while sipping on a delicious non-alcoholic beverage

adr_address: 442 Geary Street, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 442 Geary Street, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Today was pretty rough at this location- the service was great (the girl at the cash was very sweet) however they were extremely understaffed and you could tell that the staff were feeling overwhelmed. I waited 20 Minutes for a breakfast sandwich and a cappuccino. It wasn't a big deal for me since I am on vacation but I am sure that someone who was heading in to work would have been extremely inconvenienced. I felt bad for the gentleman who was on the coffee bar as he clearly could have used a second set of hands there. He really did a great job, despite this. He seemed to have a system for the coffee and as he made coffees he listened to customers complaints about the wait and was still extremely professional and courteous.

Great place, little small with very few sits. The high table is very small, of course enough for coffee and a snack, but forget about anything else. It is in tenderloin so you do get few homeless people trying to come in and use restrooms.
Nice drinks and friendly staff. Although they sometimes mess up my order i just ask them to make it the way i ordered it and they gladly make it again without charge (obviously)
Need to do a better job keeping the dining room clean.
Great Starbucks and friendly staff. Busy but efficient with the line and  a lot of foreign visitors. Wonderful energy from everyone who works there.

adr_address: 384 Hayes St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 384 Hayes St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Arlequin Cafe & Food-To-Go

reviews.text: Cosy coffee with charming outside area. Oatmeal and Homemade Granola were great, they also have a lot of options for lunch.

My laptop was stolen at this location on a Saturday evening. Somewhat unhelpfully I was informed that none of the cameras situated at the premises actually work. Management were extremely unhelpful and made little attempt (essentially none) to assist. Be advised to maintain a keen eye on any and all possessions while at this restaurant.
Very relaxing environment! Great food and drinks! Great place to study!

A tried and true go to with one of the best garden patios in the city (though beware of chirping birds pooping on you). Food here is reliably good - salads are fresh and I'd recommend the pork breakfast burrito (served until 4pm). Enjoy!
Food was really good but they lost our ticket and we had to track down the server to get our food order actually put in and they didn't really seem apologetic about it and took a long time.

adr_address: 462 Powell St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 462 Powell St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Very busy location. Unfortunately our coffee tasted very different than usual so we questions the barista and received attitude in return. I had noticed them run or of the syrup used in my coffee just as mine was ready. They reluctantly remade the coffee after a bit of further attitude. The coffee then tasted as normal... Amazing. Will probably go elsewhere as there are many to choose from within a 5 min walk.
Awesome...FYI This location is the Number One Busiest Store In USA
Had annearly bird coffee. Friendly people, well located. Liked it❣️
Clean and service is great. The wait time can't be helped, due to it being off of Union Square.

Standard Starbucks that's a little on the smaller side so difficult to find seating in the couple of times I visited. Staff are very quick even though the location is rather busy so a great option if you're looking to just grab coffee and go.

adr_address: 67 5th St, San Francisco, CA 94103-1812, USA
formatted_address: 67 5th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Cafe Venue

reviews.text:
Good, quick breakfast and lunch service made to order. They have a small selection of pastries, too, and good coffee, but it's not my favorite coffee in the area. Prices are reasonable for the location and this is one of my favorite places to stop for breakfast in this area, usually for a breakfast sandwich to go. 

They have bagels, too, but only a limited amount daily (they don't make their own baked goods) and while they are decent for SF they are nothing special and don't really ease the craving for NY/NJ-style bagel shop bagels. (Panera bagels are probably about the same or maybe even a bit better, if only because there are more options.)

Since this is SF, they also have a decent selection of gluten-free options on the menu (but mostly of the "as a salad" or "hold the bread" type) if that's what you're looking for.
The breakfast is nice but the service is not so good. The attendant was rude and impatient. Blueberry smoothie is awesome as much as the Guatemala coffee.
Great value for breakfast in DTSF. Loved the avocado toast.
Friendly fast service and tasty food
Strong, yet smooth, double espresso. Amazingly light and flaky cheese Danish. Excellent service from friendly staff. Kudos!

adr_address: 212 Ritch St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
formatted_address: 212 Ritch St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: Darwin Cafe

reviews.text: Simple menu. Tasty salads and sandwiches. You’ll probably spend $12-15 on lunch. A great healthier choice.
Great sandwiches!! Nice restaurant. Some tables inside and outside!

Food: meh. Portions are tiny for the price. I'm not sure why people frequent here.

Cleanliness: pretty dirty here. The last time I was there, the chef was sitting on the table where he prepared food with his disgusting jeans, playing on his phone. I was very grossed out by that. They also always have the doors wide open, and flies are everywhere from the dirty streets of SOMA.

Service: poor. The staff aren't particularly attentive to the needs of the customers.
Lovely roast beef. A little pricey.
This was the only take out coffee shop around the area. It looked like a hipster cafe. I liked their Americano. The pastry was delicious too.

adr_address: McKesson Plaza, 1 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
formatted_address: McKesson Plaza, 1 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
name: Specialty's Cafe & Bakery

reviews.text: Chilli bowl soul is very delicious, full of flavor. Not very good customer service
Great sandwiches, salads and sides. Oh and cookies!!! Delish!!

This place is all over San Francisco and one of the identities of the city. It was right outside my office and I could see office crowd there many times. 

Coffee and Food:
While they make really good latte and mocha, their egg & cheddar sandwich and butter croissant are perfect companions for the coffee. Especially, the egg and cheddar sandwich was brilliant. I haven't had much chance of tasting other things but I am sure they are all great. 

Ambiance:
It is quite spacious and comfortable seating options. Overall, a great place to relax and unwind over a cup of coffee and some delicious food. 

Staff:
When we talk about chain cafes, there is only one thing that differentiates one location from the other - the staff. This one has a great staff. The lady at the counter was very welcoming and tried to engage with every customer in one way or the other while taking the orders. The rest of the staff was very helpful as well. It is always great to visit this place. 

Overall, a great place to be and if you're in San Francisco, you can't escape Peet's.

Most pathetic breakfast sandwich I've ever had.
Scrambled eggs over cooked bacon.
The bread was good . That's about it.

It was just all right. Cookies were a tad bit old, and the atmosphere was hot, and not in a good way. They need air conditioning, and even tho it was late in the day them cookies should've been fresh. McDies has better cookies at times, so I was disappointed. :-(

vicinity: McKesson Plaza, 1 Post Street, San Francisco

adr_address: 437 Hayes St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 437 Hayes St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Chantal Guillon Macarons

reviews.text: Huge selection of different flavors. These are French macarons and quite delicate.  If you have a special event coming up, they can even customize some for you.

Absolutely the most delicious Macarons in all of San Francisco. Their unique flavors are not overwhelming, but are delicate and flavorful, such as the Persian Rose and Earl Grey, which are both a must buy. In addition their traditional flavors are all perfectly executed. You might not find a better Pistachio in all of California.
This place offers an amazing variety of mouth watering flavors! To top it off, the macarons are freshly prepared. I recommend the apple caramel and passion fruit flavors!

This place is a tasty little gem.  The store is brightly lit, showing off their treats in display counter.  We came here and got a box of 12, they let you hand pick the flavors.  I suggest buying only what you can eat in a couple of days and storing it in the frig.  Allow them to come to room temperature before eating.  I really like that they give you a flavor menu to go with your box.  The people who run the store is super friendly.  We can't wait to go back again.

Macarons aren't a treat that I've ever been partial to. However, I stopped in on a whim with a friend, and we both agreed that this place is absolutely amazing. They are more cakey than the macarons I've had in the past, and the flavor & texture is phenomenal. I went back this week and grabbed a few to share with coworkers, who all agreed that it was one of the best macarons they'd ever had—one even decided to start using this as her go to gift for teacher appreciation celebrations.

adr_address: 150 Stockton St, Level Four, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
formatted_address: 150 Stockton St, Level Four, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
name: The Rotunda

reviews.text:
Perfect for a snack or quick lunch. 
I had a sandwich and it was delicious. The service was quick and the price fair.

I've been to the Rotunda 4 times now and have never had a bad experience with food or service here. I've came in dressed up and super casual and the staff had been very courteous either way.

It gets busy very quickly so do reserve your table in advance.

Recommended: Lobster bisque (a cup is very filling so order moderately if you do get the bisque!).

PS: You could also get a decent tea time here($45/person) with lots of interesting tea blends and sweet/savory bites.

One of my favorite restaurants from the food to the service.  Amazing!  One request.  Please, please bring back your Tuscan Chicken Sandwich.  It is so good and I used to order it every single time I visited.  Please and thank you.  :)

100% LOVE The Rotunda. Flawless with superb food and perfect service. Whether w/ family to enjoy formal afternoon tea that my Mom always had here when we visited SanFran (BTW, thank you Nanette M for introducing me to top SanFran eateries) or for business lunch or dinner with KKR, Wells Fargo (old First Security pals), etc.
The popovers and strawberry butter are worth the whole meal. The staff was very cheerful.

vicinity: 150 Stockton St, Level Four, San Francisco

adr_address: 490 Brannan St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
formatted_address: 490 Brannan St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: I love starbucks they have good customer service and really good coffee on point white chocolate mocha latte sweet with carmel and chocolate

Certain baristas fail to read the instructions on my cup. Today I was served a drink with almond milk and I have an allergy to tree nuts!!!! I'm really disappointed with the lack of training at this location.

Starbucks is great, employees are nice.  BUT IF YOU DRIVE A CAR YOU WILL BE HARRASSED BY RECEIVING A FAKE TICKET FROM PCSPARKING SERVICES.  THIS TICKET IS UNENFORCEABLE.  THEY HAVE BEEN SUED IN 2007 FOR THIS PRACTICE AND LOST BUT CONTINUE TO "SEE WHAT THEY CAN GET.". THE TICKET LOOKS LIKE THIS. But STARBUCKS is Great, not their fault.
Friendly staff and the green tea frappuchino tastes great
One of the only coffee places for blocks, they are super busy in the mornings. They run out of food a lot. Friendly staff.

adr_address: 754 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94109-6176, USA
formatted_address: 754 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
name: Farm : Table

reviews.text: Nice hole in the wall hipster cafe. Had a great SO Ethiopian there. Flavour lingered for a good hour after I finished it. Food options are small portioned but fresh and tasty side snacks. Be careful if walking to it from the  downhill tenderloin area.

A busy little coffee shop that you must visit if you are in the area. Homemade almond milk is so good and the Breakfast goodies are excellent. It takes a bit to get the order so be patient. A lot of people go here and it is very small and run by only a couple people. It's worth the wait. The cereal is quite good. As is the egg on croissant.

This place is absolutely outstanding. The charcoal latte was something I have never tried before, but it was very good. My favorite item is the egg sandwich. I always come here when I am in town and I definitely recommend it.

Great small neighborhood breakfast place. Interesting selection of coffee and tea drinks. Good is great but there is not much room to sit. We did take out. Definitely going back next time I am in the area
Great croissant with egg and avocado. One of those tasty and healthy places I like very much. Cool SF stuff.

adr_address: 160 7th St, San Francisco, CA 94103-4901, USA
formatted_address: 160 7th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Caffe Moda

reviews.text: The breakfast sandwich that i had was great, but the secret is in the waffles. My sister had one and said it was the best waffle she's had anywhere in a long time.  Delicious milk shakes and smoothies. Very friendly service, and decent prices. Will definitely go back if I'm in the area again. (This breakfast was better than the one that i had to pay for at my hotel)
Very friendly lady who always makes the best smoothies
Their breakfast is bad compared to the price, and what you can find other places nearby.
Great customer service, good and clean place, the food was okay, but the too pricy

This establishment is right across from the best western and is AMAZING!! I absolutely loved their waffles and the service was great. Whenever I come to san francisco this is my new go to breakfast spot!!

adr_address: 709 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94109-7116, USA
formatted_address: 709 Larkin St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
name: Quickly

reviews.text: By far the best boba tea place I've ever stumbled across. Prices are pretty average. They always make my order perfect and I highly recommend.
The food isn't quick but the food does taste great. Would recommend a chicken wing rice bowl.

They're really yummy, but only take cash and uh the illegal pawn shop in the corner of the shop and the shady people who visit it stare you down while you're ordering so it definitely doesn't feel safe lol
Rose slush, shall I say more?

Don't care about customer service . Always have their kids behind the counter and also let all the street people in so they can buy their stolen electronics. Only thing that's consistent is asking me if I want to make it a large or add toppings .

adr_address: 333 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
formatted_address: 333 Stockton St, San Francisco, CA 94108, USA
name: Emporio Rulli

reviews.text:
I knew I was trouble when I saw fleas on the bagels.

The absolute worst restaurant experience in the 11 years I have lived in SF.  I ordered a small quiche and a cappuccino.  Nothing but a pure ripoff.  For $11.35 I got a cappuccino in a 3 oz. trial size cup.  After asking why I wasn't being served in a regular coffee cup, the young lady explained that I did not request it.  Who serves a coffee in trial size cup when you are dining in?  

The quiche consisted of four small bites of stale bread.  The young lady could not have been more rude on top of this scam.

Three sips and four small bites for $11. This is the worse of SF "gotcha" culture.

The cafe in the Square does a great coffee and seems to specialise in pastries. Nice outside seating. Pretty busy location right in the square. 

The cakes unfortunately need to be closed in away from flies. 

The staff really friendly and know their pastries. The price of coffee was cheaper than larger main steam coffee shops.

Extremely pricey, terrible slow service with heavy attitude, and no menus. Two stars just because the location is ideal on the square for a nice day.

Would recommend just grabbing a drink maybe and then heading to Tunnel Top, Mikkeller Bar, or Burritt Room.

I've known this place for years, always bustling, always busy. Lately the service is surly and indifferent, the bread is stale the only thing I enjoyed was the latte was acceptable. I hate it when a place takes advantage of it's stunning location to give you mediocrity.
You re the best !Thank u soo mich

adr_address: 2 Henry Adams St, San Francisco, CA 94103-5016, USA
formatted_address: 2 Henry Adams St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Caffe Pazzo

reviews.text: This is a great place to grab a quick bite. It has some amazing sandwiches. You can either get entire sandwich or you can get half sandwich and soup. They also give free bread and butter as appetizers for free .There are only few places in the area where you can dine in for under $11 and this is one of them. Definitely check it out.

Food is nothing to alter your lunch plans for. A bit over priced for what you actually get. $12-15 salads after tax is a bit much for "ok" tasting. Pretty fast ordering and to-go is a large draw to eat here.
Fast, good lunch with several options for salads or sandwiches.  Perfect size for lunch.  Free bread and olive oil at a self serve station as well!
Wonderful lunch options!
This is a great spot for a mid day lunch. They have some health options and some less healthy. I like the meatball sandwich. This place is in the same resturant group as Dos Pinas a few blocks away.

adr_address: 470 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 470 Post St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Cafe La Taza

reviews.text:
Very average food and extremely overpriced. I payed $26 for an egg scramble with (not so great) orange juice and mashed potatoes on the side. Ridiculous.

Also the place looks much nicer in pictures. It looks more like a rundown diner than a cute cafe. If you want a cute cafe, there's a nice looking place next door.
Quaint cafe. Only Vegetarian opton is like sandwiches which was pretty good. Not exactly cheap for a sandwich but what do you expect for the middle of SF.

Grace makes the BEST Caramel Frappe! It's loaded with 3 shots. Better than Starbucks!

The food is delicious and unique.  A bit pricey but it is in Union Square so you should expect the higher prices. The food is worth the extra few bucks. I heard they have a sister location in the Mission that is super good too!

This place has some fantastic sandwiches.  They're a little pricey, but not more than what you would typically find in this part of San Francisco.  I came here several times during my stay and I really enjoyed it.  The wait wasn't too long either, even when they were busy.
Place its good tasting try the fresh oj juice 🥤..from houston,tx

adr_address: 170 O'Farrell St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 170 O'Farrell St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: When I was at the Starbucks, it was slow. I mean i get it if they had a lot of customers. But the people who ordered after me got their drinks right away while i had to wait 7-9 minutes for my drinks. I also ordered a croissant which the barista got wrong and gave to somebody else. I ended up with a drink that I waited on for a long time and no croissant. Also a man spoke up since a few others were waiting and the workers sort of yelled back really rudely, saying they don't have time or to go somewhere else if they want fast service. And they were still complaining after. Note that I was almost late too.
The manager is very kind and awesome. He even remembers some of customers' names and tries his best!
Good service, many options, good food
Visited this Starbucks during the holidays and the line was ridiculous.   The Barista's were nice and my drink was excellent.

reviews.author_name: A B M Jabed Sultan Pias
reviews.text: Wonderful place to have a cup of coffee. This starbucks is popular in such crowded place.

formatted_address: 865 Market Street, C 26A, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Kinda busy for only one barista.. but considering, good service.
Rampant theft and smelly people.  The cashiers serve people who obviously budge in line and then just shrug it off.
Quick and convenient - it's on the floor of Westfield Centre that leads to Powell BART station exit.

I doubt whether THE RACIST is still working in this shop! Two years have been past, I cannot forget the humiliation.

Watch out the racist in this shop!!!
When I ordered my coffee, one of the staff(big fat african-american)asked me again as if he didn't understand my word. It's ok. But, when I told my name, he asked me three times, then giggled at me. Then I knew that he was playing with me. Suddenly, he said "WHAT RACE ARE YOU?" I couldn't believe... It was impossible he didn't know it. Because one of his coleague was also asian-american.
How dare he asked me that rude question.
I made some complaint about his rude attitude but I think he will do that racial discriminative behavior again, for sure.
I never understand starbucks how such a racist can be hired as a staff...
starbucks must have no screening system...
Very fast service and prices are reasonable and comparable to any other Starbucks not in the city center

adr_address: 400 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102-4512, USA
formatted_address: 400 McAllister St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Mint Cafe

reviews.text: If you're stuck in the building doing jury duty and you just want to order a coffee and eat the lunch you brought, you're out of luck. Never mind that half the tables are empty -- you will be asked to leave, because there's no outside food allowed and rules are rules.

adr_address: 7 3rd St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 7 3rd St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Starbucks

reviews.text: Cool place to come and grab a drink. My order took a long time even though there were about 2 people in the place at the time but it’s cool.

Probably one of the worst locations I’ve ever visited. The staff allows the homeless to use the bathroom to “shower” and clean up. Two homeless men were having sex in the bathroom on my last visit. I mean...good for them but....umm...yikes. Extremely rude staff. The place was filthy. Girls behind the counter were chatting and ignoring customers. One was sipping her own drink while people were waiting for their breakfast sandwiches that she forgot to put in the oven. Then she gave attitude when people asked. One walked away from the register while she was ringing up a lady. She was gone for 60 secs. The lady looks at me like “Can I take my chip card out?” Yikes. There are plenty of other options within a block or two.
Pretty slow service. They take your order right away but then you stand there waiting for it way longer than necessary. It tasted good, though.

I've never felt so compelled to write a bad review !The reason I frequent Starbucks is simple - decent Internet connectivity and plug points for charging, aside from some decent coffee. This is supposed to be the "Starbucks experience" after all. If it were just for the coffee, there are far better indie places out there. And hence I find it unacceptable when this location seals their plug points so that patrons cannot charge their devices.

More so, I would have loved to smack the staff for their downright condescending attitude!  I got a Protein Box and asked for cutlery - the looks and attitude shown by the staff was as if I had stolen a Protein Box! I was turned down for Salt, Pepper and Sriracha with zero eye-contact and curt replies.

Store manager - kindly take note. Do not ruin the "Starbucks experience".

Bathroom was filthy dirty and gross!
Drinks were normal.
Staff busy and friendly.  Yet, since when does "no problem" replace "your welcome" as a curtious reply to a customer's "thank you"?
Someone better work on better customer relations.

adr_address: 36 5th St, San Francisco, CA 94103-1811, USA
formatted_address: 36 5th St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Mo'z Cafe

reviews.text: Decent prices, decent food, and a great selection of choices. I had a salmon scramble for brunch and it was tasty, but not amazing. There definitely could have been more salmon in it. The crepe was a little better but I felt a little like maybe it wasn't quite sweet enough. Despite that, the price point is good enough that it's worth going to even if the food is slightly lacking in some areas.

Ate here for breakfast. The first striking thing about this place is what a big (and awesome) menu it has! Lots of great stuff for all tastes. We had the waffle and eggs Benedict. Both dishes were excellent, but the waffle was truly stand out - the waffle itself used a really good and tasty batter. The ordering / service is a bit strange (order first then get your table), but very attentive nine the less! I would definitely recommend this place!

Nice Place to have a breakfast with friendly staff. The coffee was excellent. The food was not the best i ve ever ate but it was worth the money. Another pro is the cozy athmosphere. So have a breakfast, lunch and a coffee

Delicious breakfast burritos here. They're pretty busy on the weekends, but the line moves fast. 

I love how empty it is during the day on Weekdays. They have plenty of outlets for working. WiFi but I've never tried it. & the atmosphere is fantastic when empty. High ceilings & big pretty bars make it feel nice. Highly suggest for remote workers during the work day, just being headphones for music. Many outlets near all the windows.
Big menu, good and fresh food. Homeless guy came in and grabbed my pancaces with his hands and run off. Shocking experience, but I got new pancaces from friendly staff.

adr_address: 198 Gough St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 198 Gough St, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: 20th Century Cafe

reviews.text: French Toast, Reuben sandwich, Hot Chocolate and Russian Honey Cake were out of this world-good. Having said that, the place as a whole is fairly expensive for what it offers. At about $30/person, ood for special occasions but not for regular visits.

Great cafe with incredible baked goods. I'm a HUGE fan of their freshly made bagels. A bit pricey but they are socially conscious and are currently donating 25% of all proceeds to social justice causes. The space itself is a throwback to the art deco era with an artful tin wrapped counter area, wall sconces, and a charming striped awning outside. Great place to relax and indulge.

The food and ambiance here are 5+ stars. The service has always been chaotic -- often slow, and the tables can take forever to be cleared.  And as they are cleared people behind you in line might grab them.  I think the customer experience here would be improved if the staff focused on fundamentals of getting orders taken and customers seated somewhat quickly. Maybe that's too 21st Century but I think it's a nice courtesy.

Original decoration on Art Deco theme with dressed waitresses in the same theme. The pastries are good and fine. red tea to taste, light and slightly spicy. Finally the chocolate is most surprising. We feel the good taste of dark chocolate powder. Very good!
Delicious pastries. If you want to treat you have to visit this place. Thanks Michelle and staff for your excellent customer service and your in the way you all prepare these delicious pastries

adr_address: 199 Sutter St, San Francisco, CA 94104-4501, USA
formatted_address: 199 Sutter St, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA
name: Bread and Cocoa

reviews.text: The food looked decent, but my drink was not. The almond milk was burnt, and the espresso underneath tasted dead. I ordered it for here, but they gave it in a paper cup. And, as I sat in a far corner, I couldn't hear my drink being called. Which is fine, I would have gone up in a moment to check on it. Instead the barista came over to tell me the drink was ready, but rather than hand it to me it was seated on the far side of the counter, meaning I had to walk around the horseshoe bar to get it then walk back. Not a huge expenditure of energy, but the customer service was lacking. My friends did, however, enjoy their sandwiches.

Once again, my tomato allergy gets in the way of a decent lunch. I ordered the special - Caesar salad with chicken. Why? Because Caesar salad generally doesn't have tomatoes in it. But here, according to the chef it does.  How am I supposed to know that? I ordered it for here, it comes in a "to go" box. By the time I get it and discover a half dozen cherry tomatoes sliced in half with tomato juiced squeezed all over my salad, I don't have time to re-order, though the chef did offer, after he set me straight about HIS way of making a Caesar salad. (Besides, nothing else seemed tomato free on the menu). I picked out the chicken and left, hoping my allergies won't flare this afternoon.  If you're going to play with a classic dish, make sure you note the ingredients on the sign board.
Very fast and very good. I got the Paris breakfast sandwich and a large coffee. Both very delicious and for a very reasonable price. Will definitely go back.

A very tasty, warm and loving place to get breakfast! I was looking for somewhere to have breakfast before heading to the post office and popped in and it was delicious! The staff are friendly as well
Decent sandwich, great coffee. The chicken pesto sandwich was ok. Tasted good and a nice size. Really enjoyed the iced coffee. I'd go again just for it.

adr_address: 149 New Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
formatted_address: 149 New Montgomery St, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA
name: Cafe Madeleine

reviews.text: I love this cafe s breads especially on the right  side of the counter maybe including strawberry jam?

The matcha cake is excellent and not too sweet.  Fast service.  Pretty pricey though!  

The decor is a bit plain.

They don't have a huge selection or menu but what they do have is fancy, tasty, elegant and expensive.
I decided to get three things today. I got the mocha (which I had remembered from coming here a long time ago was very rich and tasty). I also got a kale, avacado and tomato salad which looked appealing and surprised me with how flavorful it was. I also a chicken and artichoke sandwich that was quite good as well. This place is a bit more pricey (even for SOMA standards) but the quality certainly was appropriate for the price and the staff was very friendly and helpful.
Great local cafe with fabulous mocha and hot chocolates that are topped with chocolate whipped cream.  The cakes and pastries are really good here.
Adorable place, enjoy the food and drinks!

adr_address: 426 Brannan St, San Francisco, CA 94107-1714, USA
formatted_address: 426 Brannan St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: Brickhouse Cafe

reviews.text: We go here occasionally and really like the food for either dinner or weekend brunch (pancake-fried bacon is worth a try!). They had some live music a few times, but that was years ago--I don't think they do it anymore, but was great! Some of the seating is old chairs that aren't comfortable, would love if they'd replace those.

They served me beef stroganoff with no sour cream because they were out.  They waited until it came to table to tell me.  I could not order anything else because they were closing.  They only offered a free drink after that.  I did not eat the food which was like 20 bucks. The drink was good.

Love to go there to eat pancakes and french toasts at weekend's morning. Their pancake have tasty strawberry's preserve. But if you want to eat a big breakfast, it might not have a big one. French toast is pretty big. You can choose hamburgers (big one!) from morning too. Also their coffee is good. Staffs are friendly, and inside the restaurant is cozy.
Super cool staff and great customers. Their coffee is great. Glad i passed by everyday on my way to class.

Rustic and homey feeling. The Burgers seem to be the main attraction on the menu but my quinoa salad was fresh and wonderful. 
Not packed on the Monday night I was there. Great for a low key dinner or a sweet romantic one on one.

adr_address: 601 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
formatted_address: 601 Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94102, USA
name: Peet's Coffee

reviews.text:
A friend and I went in for a coffee and a bagel, both of which were satisfactory. The girl who served me however ruined the experience. Her name was Jenn, it was 12:15pm on Labor Day. Neither me or my friend could believe the responses we received to very reasonable questions such as "how big is a medium?" or "can you toast the bagel?". She was incredibly indignant and spoke to us like we were morons. 

She may have just been having a bad day, but I myself have worked in similar environment and have never been so insulting even in my lowest moods. 

Apart from her behaviour, the food and coffee were absolutely fine, and I would still recommend Peet's. 

Just posting this review in the hope that management see it and keep a closer eye on how she handles customers.
This is a great place to get coffee and read a book at the book store. The line is often long but the staff is great and moves fast.
The staff are super friendly, and if you come in at the right time, they serenade the entire shop.

I've only been to this Peet's 3 times. 2 times they have got my order wrong. One of those two times they got it wrong again even after asking them to correct the order. 

Time 1: Ordered a cappuccino. Got an Americano. They were nice enough to give me a free drink voucher. 

Time 2: ordered a cappuccino. Got a cappuccino, although it was a medium when I asked for small (wasn't gonna complain)

Time 3: ordered a cappuccino and an iced green tea with no sweetener. Got a cappuccino and a hot green tea latte (some matcha thing?). I asked them for what I ordered. An iced green tea with no sweetener. They came back with the same matcha latte drink but over ice. It was sweetened as well... I gave up and left.
Excellent service and Royale (my barista) was great. He was warm , friendly and efficient.

adr_address: 470 3rd St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
formatted_address: 470 3rd St, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA
name: Dartealing Lounge

reviews.text: Nice and cozy atmosphere. Scones weren't as soft as I expected. The finger sandwich was good but limited to one kind only for the king tea.

Utterly delightful. We had the Covent Garden high tea and everything was exquisite - the sandwiches, the scones, the little treats...just wonderful. Huge selection of teas. Cute, cozy, slightly kitschy decor -  will definitely be going back!

Tremendous selection of teas. My son doesn't like tea so he had hot chocolate "best ever" he said.

The food was quite right - you get to select from about twenty adventurous varieties. For next time we will try the "fish and chips" because we overheard others raving about it. 

The pastries were beautiful, the scones were nice - only critique would be that they should have jam as well as cream with them.

But overall a very nice time that I and my kids really enjoyed as a nice break from the hurly-burly of city life.

Very cute tea house! Wonderful atmosphere with beautiful decorations. The food is also delicious. The sandwiches and pastries are fresh and pair well with the tea options. Great for a birthday party with the girls
All day brunch place, limited seating. Nice tea collection with friendly staff.

adr_address: 433 S Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 433 S Van Ness Ave, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Flying Pig Bistro Pub

reviews.text: While waiting to check-in to our airbnb, we stumbled into this gem of a place. It was my first trip to the States from Dubai and I absolutely loved the neighborhood feel. Unbelievably friendly staff and amazing food. The bartender(an amazing guy) (I wish I could remember his name) (so that I can personally thank him) introduced us to some regulars who(Carl) showed us around town and made it a night to remember! Thank you
Very relaxed. Excellent hot dog. Got the spiced pork World Series dog. Wife got a chili cheese dog. Was really empty on a Sunday night. Perfect quiet eatery. Good beer too.
Great place a beer and food, very cozy and feels like an extension of your home.
Been going here for years. Excellent beer selection. Bottomless mimosas every day until like 3. Fun, local trivia on Tuesdays.
Awesome guy at the bar. So friendly and outgoing. Great food and cool just to hang out. Thanks a lot!

vicinity: 433 South Van Ness Avenue, San Francisco

adr_address: 442 Hyde St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
formatted_address: 442 Hyde St, San Francisco, CA 94109, USA
name: Hooker's Sweet Treats

reviews.text: Great place! Excellent coffee and good caramel bars for 2$!

Best bread pudding!
Hooker is a great guy. From the Deep South Bayou Teche. He makes delicious caramels, cookies, and bread pudding du jour. My favorite is the lemon blueberry bread pudding. Ask him for the lagniappe. 
Hook can teach you a lot about southern manners, sweets, love, life, mexico and the list goes on! So stop in here for a chat! 
Leave your ipad and laptop at home. 
Much obliged,
Hook big kiss mwah!
-Cher bebe

Great coffee and chocolate!  My wife and I walked in by chance and she was immediately hooked by the sea salt caramel chocolate that was available. We added two cappuccinos and we're off. Before we could leave, we had to get a wonderful smelling scone. A definite treat in SF.
One of the best places in San Francisco for a quality coffee and treat... love it

So good.  This is the coolest sweet shop.  It's a great addition to the neighborhood.  Favorites are the salted caramels and the bread pudding.
HOWEVER: PLEASE, PLEASE expand your hours.  Would love to be able to hang out here in the early evening.  Something like this could really turn around the area.

adr_address: 1246 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
formatted_address: 1246 Folsom St, San Francisco, CA 94103, USA
name: Vega Coffee

reviews.text: Best spot to grab a cup in this part of town...small location but the coffee is thee best...cento for life!!

This place is great. Always fast even if there's a small line. But even if there is, the owner is always talkative. And the coffee is great. I usually get a macchiato which has good balance but it can sometimes taste like the espresso is a little under or over extracted. Overall I love this place. 

It is cash only!! So be careful of that one.
Vega is great! Raoul and co. are always friendly and helpful. Try their home-made oat bars.

Best cappuccino in the city - never burnt, always perfect! I've had it here at least 20 times (worked nearby) and it's so much better than Sightglass' and Blue Bottle's. The staff is friendly, especially the slightly round guy whose name I forget. The owner refused to take shortcuts, which is amazing. Also good croissants (get them before they run out, before 8:30 usually).
Raoul was great! We appreciated the friendly  conversation and sending off with coffee beans to try at home. Vega Cafe is a wonderful find in SOMA.

Very good cappuccino. Food items seemed average and overpriced.
Free internet. Fresh, hand dripped coffee, superb food. Aces all around.
Nice coffee. Free and fast WiFi.
Tasty coffee and nice people but the service is a bit slow.

name: Peet's Coffee

reviews.text:
It's a good establishment, especially compared to other locations closer to and on market. It gets crowded sometimes, but it doesn't stay crowded. They have 9 small circle tables and 1 slightly bigger square table, but they are not all crammed together. Electrical outlets are on the wall parallel to 4th st.

Staff are nice and provide good service. They keep the place clean. The music is not too loud. Comfortable setting.
Get my weekend Mochas here and couldn't be more pleased w/ the staff, service and hand-crafted drinks.
Great service and staff! -- they brought me a replacement drink after I spilled mine all over my laptop and helped clean it.
Quite few sitting places here and you won't find one during busy hours. Other than that this is a nice place
A fun place to get a cup of coffee after your lunch across the street from Whole Foods Market SoMa
